</figureCitation>
) sparsely covered with short, yellowish, strongly retrorsely, decumbent setae.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1242,1171,1194]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277139/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" targetBox="[158,1409,191,1150]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1242,1171,1194]" box="[151,1242,1171,1194]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,314,1171,1194]" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">FIGURES 1–2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[320,645,1172,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Ischalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barclayi" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Nitidischalia">
